Drives phase 2 of the cage lifecycle: starts the API proxy (billed modes only), execs the caged process under `bwrap` with stdio inherited, and stops the proxy after the cage exits.

`run_until_exit(r: &Resolved, prep: &Prep) -> Result<i32, CageError>` is the entry point. It starts the proxy only if `mode_is_billed(&r.mode)`, always execs the cage, then signals `stop` on the proxy's `AtomicBool` and joins its thread regardless of exit status — the join result is discarded, so proxy-thread errors are silently dropped. Returns the cage's exit code (defaults to 1 if the process was killed by a signal, per `ExitStatus::code()`).

`start_proxy` binds a Unix socket at `prep.rundir/API_SOCK_NAME` (removing any stale file first), spawns the proxy accept loop (`proxy::serve`) on a background thread, and uses **passthrough auth**: `ProxyConfig.api_key` is `None`, so the caged process's own `Authorization` header goes straight through to `api.anthropic.com` — no key injection here despite proxying billed traffic.

`exec_cage` builds a `BwrapConfig` from `Resolved`/`Prep` (secret masks, tool binds, rw binds, env, rules path) and runs `bwrap` via `Command`, skipping argv[0] since `build_bwrap_args` includes the program name at index 0. `new_session` is set to `!interactive` — interactive mode keeps the session so terminal control (Ctrl-C, job control) works.

`cage_cmd_for_mode` dispatches per `Mode`: `SelfTestStub` runs a containment self-check script, `Task`/`Interactive` run claude headless or not. The self-test script (`self_test_stub_cmd`) is a load-bearing invariant check — it verifies workspace writability, that secret masks are *readable-as-empty* rather than unreadable (a prior mask implementation broke git this way), git functions, and network is blocked (via a socat probe to 1.1.1.1:80). It writes only under `target/` per ADR-027 and is cwd-relative per ADR-046 — changing cwd assumptions elsewhere in the lifecycle breaks this script.

`claude_cmd` starts an in-cage `socat` relay forwarding `127.0.0.1:8080` → the bind-mounted proxy socket at `/run/ctx/{API_SOCK_NAME}` (this path must match wherever the socket is bind-mounted into the cage — coupled to `bwrap.rs`'s mount setup), then execs `claude` with `--dangerously-skip-permissions`, relying on the cage itself as the sandbox boundary that flag assumes. Headless mode passes `-p` and reads the task brief from `$CTX_TASK_BRIEF`; interactive mode omits both.

`API_SOCK_NAME`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`, `BwrapConfig`, and `build_bwrap_args` are defined in `crate::bwrap` and must stay in sync with the mount/env setup this file assembles.